SCENARIO-BASED GIT COMMANDS (ONE-LINE ANSWERS)
ðŸ”¹ 1. Start a new project

Command:

git init


Meaning: Create a new Git repository.

ðŸ”¹ 2. Connect local project to GitHub

Command:

git remote add origin <repo-url>


Meaning: Link your project to a GitHub repository.

ðŸ”¹ 3. Check changes in your files

Command:

git status


Meaning: Shows modified/untracked files.

ðŸ”¹ 4. Add a single changed file

Command:

git add filename


Meaning: Stage one file for commit.

ðŸ”¹ 5. Add all changed files

Command:

git add .


Meaning: Stage all files for commit.

ðŸ”¹ 6. Save (commit) your work

Command:

git commit -m "message"


Meaning: Save staged changes with a message.

ðŸ”¹ 7. Push code to GitHub (first time)

Command:

git push -u origin main


Meaning: Upload commits and set main as default branch.

ðŸ”¹ 8. Push updates next time

Command:

git push


Meaning: Upload new commits to GitHub.

ðŸ”¹ 9. Pull latest code from GitHub

Command:

git pull


Meaning: Bring latest changes from remote repository.

ðŸ”¹ 10. Clone an existing GitHub project

Command:

git clone <repo-url>


Meaning: Copy a repo to your system.

ðŸ”¹ 11. Create a new branch

Command:

git checkout -b feature1


Meaning: Create and switch to a new branch.

ðŸ”¹ 12. Switch to an existing branch

Command:

git checkout feature1


Meaning: Move to another branch.

ðŸ”¹ 13. Merge a branch into main

Command:

git merge feature1


Meaning: Combine branch changes into main.

ðŸ”¹ 14. Delete a branch after merging

Command:

git branch -d feature1


Meaning: Remove a local branch.

ðŸ”¹ 15. View commit history

Command:

git log --oneline


Meaning: See short commit history.

ðŸ”¹ 16. Undo last commit (keep changes)

Command:

git reset --soft HEAD~1


Meaning: Remove commit but keep files staged.

ðŸ”¹ 17. Undo last commit (remove everything)

Command:

git reset --hard HEAD~1


Meaning: Delete commit and changes permanently.

ðŸ”¹ 18. Remove wrong remote URL

Command:

git remote remove origin


Meaning: Remove GitHub connection.

ðŸ”¹ 19. See connected remote URLs

Command:

git remote -v


Meaning: List remote repositories.

ðŸ”¹ 20. See what changed inside files

Command:

git diff
